task_description: Facing the building to your South (approx. 175°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: Moving to the front-right position (move 1) will bring me closer to the target building, providing a better perspective to observe its full height and compare with nearby reference objects for a more accurate estimate.

Moving back to the previous position (move 2) will return me to the location where I was originally facing the target building (South, ~175°), allowing me to directly view it for height estimation instead of repeatedly attempting to rotate from the current SW-facing position.
